  }, {
    "owner" : {
      "account_id" : 3723758,
      "reputation" : 13039,
      "user_id" : 3600553,
      "user_type" : "registered",
      "accept_rate" : 71,
      "profile_image" : "https://i.sstatic.net/beIr4.jpg?s=256",
      "display_name" : "Du-Lacoste",
      "link" : "https://stackoverflow.com/users/3600553/du-lacoste"
    },
    "is_accepted" : false,
    "score" : 1,
    "last_activity_date" : 1651637176,
    "creation_date" : 1651637176,
    "answer_id" : 72107810,
    "question_id" : 17561826,
    "content_license" : "CC BY-SA 4.0",
    "body" : "<p>IntelliJ IDEA caches considerable amount of files for all projects that you have ever worked with in the IDE, hence the system cache may become overloaded.</p>\n<p>Before you proceed, make note of these.</p>\n<ul>\n<li>The caches will not be deleted until you restart <code>IntelliJ IDEA</code>.</li>\n<li>Opening and closing a project without invalidating the cache does not\nresult in deleting any cached files.</li>\n<li>Local History is not deleted when you invalidate the cache unless you\nexplicitly enable this option in the Invalidate Caches dialog.</li>\n</ul>\n<p>You could do the following now via IDE to invalidate cache:</p>\n<ol>\n<li><p>From the main menu, select File | Invalidate Caches.</p>\n</li>\n<li><p>In the Invalidate Caches dialog, Click <code>Invalidate and Restart</code>.</p>\n</li>\n</ol>\n<p>If you click Just <code>restart</code>, cache files won't be deleted.</p>\n<p>You may have a look:</p>\n<p><a href=\"https://www.jetbrains.com/help/idea/invalidate-caches.html\" rel=\"nofollow noreferrer\">https://www.jetbrains.com/help/idea/invalidate-caches.html</a></p>\n"
  }, {
    "owner" : {
      "account_id" : 4607212,
      "reputation" : 1348,
      "user_id" : 3736341,
      "user_type" : "registered",
      "profile_image" : "https://i.sstatic.net/itTQkAOj.webp?s=256",
      "display_name" : "Ryan Sandberg",
      "link" : "https://stackoverflow.com/users/3736341/ryan-sandberg"
    },
    "is_accepted" : false,
    "score" : 1,
    "last_activity_date" : 1708617933,
    "last_edit_date" : 1708617933,
    "creation_date" : 1666111631,
    "answer_id" : 74114602,
    "question_id" : 17561826,
    "content_license" : "CC BY-SA 4.0",
    "body" : "<p>For me, Invalidating Cache with all options did not solve it.\nMy issue started when I upgraded from 2021-2022.2.3.</p>\n<p>What did work was deleting the IntelliJ cache folders for 2021 &amp; 2022.\nTheir location is documented here: <a href=\"https://intellij-support.jetbrains.com/hc/en-us/articles/206544519-Directories-used-by-the-IDE-to-store-settings-caches-plugins-and-logs\" rel=\"nofollow noreferrer\">https://intellij-support.jetbrains.com/hc/en-us/articles/206544519-Directories-used-by-the-IDE-to-store-settings-caches-plugins-and-logs</a></p>\n<p>For my Mac it was in located at:\n/Users/myUsername/Library/Caches/JetBrains</p>\n<p>After this, IntelliJ opened and worked as expected.</p>\n"
  }, {
    "owner" : {
      "account_id" : 26640306,
      "reputation" : 149,
